[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Redirect Status Codes                                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m | Code | Type | Method Preserved |                                           [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m |------|------|------------------|                                           [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m | 301  | Permanent | No (changes to GET) |                                   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m | 302  | Found | No (changes to GET) |                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m | 303  | See Other | No (always GET) |                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m | 307  | Temporary | Yes |                                                   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m | 308  | Permanent | Yes |                                                   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Use 307/308 knowledge when crafting redirect chains that need to preserve    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m POST data.                                                                   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Building Blocks Approach                                                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m OPEN REDIRECT BUILDING BLOCKS:                                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m 1. Parameter: identify redirect parameter name                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m 2. Protocol: http://, https://, //, javascript:, data:                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m 3. Bypass: @, encoding, unicode, null byte, HPP                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m 4. Target: external domain, javascript execution                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m 5. Chain: OAuth theft, SSRF hop, phishing                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
